issue.title: Unexpected number of informative features in test_make_regression
issue.body:
The `test_make_regression` test is failing in the nightly wheel-tests-cuml-dask pipeline with an assertion error about unexpected number of informative features. The test verifies that the distributed regression dataset generation maintains the correct number of informative features.

Failing jobs: https://github.com/rapidsai/cuml/actions/runs/14943179968/job/41983141897#step:9:3225

## Environment
- CUDA: 12.0.1
- Python: 3.12
- OS: Rocky Linux 8
- GPU: L4
- Latest driver and dependencies


## Impact
This failure indicates that the distributed regression dataset generation is not correctly maintaining the specified number of informative features when generating the dataset. This could affect any code that relies on the `make_regression` function to generate datasets with a specific number of informative features.

## Related Code
The test is located in `python/cuml/cuml/tests/dask/test_dask_datasets.py` and tests the functionality of `cuml.dask.datasets.make_regression()`.

comment.body: IIUC, https://github.com/rapidsai/cuml/actions/runs/14953480142/job/42005986832 is the same job for yesterday's run and there wasn't a failure there. So it's looking like something here is flaky. I'll keep trying to reproduce it locally.
